I would prefer that you combine this method with load(), even if it basically amounts to one big method that says:

```js
if (!originalRevision) {
  ... // use a range of data
} else {
  ... // use data from two specific revisions
}
```

Having a seperate loadBaseline() function means a lot of duplicated scaffolding code below (e.g. two seperate watch statements), which I'd prefer to avoid.

Nothing to do with your patch, but this is a little inefficient since it has to iterate through every element. Lodash's "some" function would be much better (https://lodash.com/docs#some). Since we're here we might as well do something like this:

```js
// We first determine whether the row has some visible element
var anyVisible = _.some(platform.groups, function(jobGroup) {
  return _.some(jobGroup.jobs, {visible: true});
});
var display_style = anyVisible ? "table-row" : "none";
```

